<h2><i><b>About</b></i></h2>
<p>The BT Business Enterprise Day event is
aimed at around two-hundred Year 9 or Year 10 students of mixed
ability. You are grouped together into 'businesses' who compete to be
the most successful company of the day. At the end of the day, the
most successful company will win. Winning the day is quite simple;
you must have the most cash in the bank at the end of the day!</p>
<br>
<br>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-sm-6">
<p>There are a variety of methods to gain cash: <br>
-Completing
tasks such as trading on a stock exchange <br>
-Using and managing a
'real' bank account <br>
-Corporate presentations <br>
-Negotiating<br>
-Raising capital thorugh physical and mental activities<br>
-Making cars from constituent parts such as engines and body
panels (although these cost money to purchase themselves)</p>
</div>
<div class="col-sm-6" align="right">
	<img src="https://i.vimeocdn.com/video/482413697_780x439.jpg" class="img-thumbnail" width=100% height=100%> 
</div>
</div>
<p>Ultimately, you are organising and building a factory that produces many cars at a great price.</p>
</div>
